<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="158" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="15.[113,764,631,719]" pageId="15" pageNumber="158">
<emphasis box="[151,408,631,655]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="158">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
. – Endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[581,713,631,655]" name="Madagascar" pageId="15" pageNumber="158">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, wet forest understory shade and rocky places on the High Plateau near 
<collectingRegion box="[166,312,695,719]" country="Madagascar" name="Antananarivo" pageId="15" pageNumber="158">Antananarivo</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[328,408,695,719]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[109,137,1195,1214]" captionTargetBox="[133,1451,276,1168]" captionTargetId="graphics-774@7.[782,1451,276,1168]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 2. – Distribution maps. A. Adenochloa hymeniochila (Nees) Zuloaga (stars), Panicum ambositrense A. Camus (triangles), P. andringitrense A. Camus (circles) and P. ankarense A. Camus (squares); B. Panicum brevifolium L. (stars), P. capuronii A. Camus (triangle), P. cinctum Hack. (circles) and P. crystalinum Judz. &amp; Voronts. (squares)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5724518" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5724518/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="158">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="158" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[113,764,759,975]" pageId="15" pageNumber="158">
<emphasis box="[151,207,760,783]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="158">Notes</emphasis>
. – Similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="A. Camus" authorityName="A. Camus" box="[357,663,759,783]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Panicum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="15" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="manongarivense">
<emphasis box="[357,547,760,783]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="158">P. manongarivense</emphasis>
A. Camus
</taxonomicName>
but with translucent, crystal-like, bulbous-based prickle hairs on the upper glume and lower lemma (vs smaller prickle hairs) and without auricles (vs brown membranous auricles 
<quantity box="[656,763,854,879]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="158" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.0">1–1.5 mm</quantity>
long on mature leaves). Also similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[524,625,888,911]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Panicum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="15" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mitopus">
<emphasis box="[524,625,888,911]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="158">P. mitopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but spikelets 0.9–1.1(–1.3) mm long (vs 
<quantity box="[399,520,918,943]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="15" pageNumber="158" unit="mm" value="1.4" valueMax="1.7" valueMin="1.1">1.1–1.7 mm</quantity>
long).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[113,764,759,975]" box="[151,743,949,975]" pageId="15" pageNumber="158">
This species is illustrated in VORONTSOVA (2014: 
<figureCitation box="[667,727,951,975]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[136,164,1889,1908]" captionTargetBox="[136,1474,276,1864]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 1. – A. Adenochloa hymeniochila (Nees) Zuloaga; B. Panicum andringitrense A. Camus; C. Panicum brevifolium L.; D. Panicum cinctum Hack. [A: Vorontsova et al. 602; B: Vorontsova et al. 1292; C: Unvouchered photo, Andasibe-Mantadia National Park, Madagascar; D: Rakotoarisoa &amp; Randrianavosoa SNGF 2920] [Photos: A–C: M.S. Vorontsova; D: S. Rakotoarisoa]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5724516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5724516/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="158">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
